<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="36" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="36">
Saddine et al. (2015) claimed that 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. saharicus" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" rank="species" species="saharicus">B. saharicus</taxonomicName>
was the &quot;first true deserticolous species found in Algeria&quot;, a bold claim given that 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. tunetanus" pageId="21" pageNumber="36" rank="species" species="tunetanus">B. tunetanus</taxonomicName>
(sensu Vachon 1949, part) had already been recorded for Beni 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Abbés">Abbes</normalizedToken>
by Vachon (1949, 1952), also a desert location in central west Algeria, and albeit neither localities are Erg Desert areas, Beni 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Abbés">Abbes</normalizedToken>
is in the border of the Grand Erg Occidental.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
